This paper deals with training a convolutional neural network for hyperspectral image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of pre-training, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves experiments and analysis, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
